[[File:Sannomiya-jinja (Yoshioka) torii.JPG|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Torii}}
'''Sannomiya Shrine''' (三宮神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Yoshioka, Gunma|ja|吉岡町|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kitagunma District|ja|北群馬郡|12=draft}}, {{ill|Gunma Prefecture|ja|群馬県|12=draft}}. It is a {{ill|Shikinai-sha|ja|式内社|12=draft}} ({{ill|Myōjin Taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|12=draft}}) and ranked as the third shrine ({{ill|Sannomiya|ja|三宮|12=draft}}) of {{ill|Kōzuke Province|ja|上野国|12=draft}}. Its former shrine rank was {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|村社|12=draft}}.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|和書 |first= |last=群馬県地域創生部文化財保護課 |title=群馬県近世寺社総合調査報告書－歴史的建造物を中心に－神社編 |origdate=2022-03-18 |date=2022-03-18 |url=https://sitereports.nabunken.go.jp/121895 |location=群馬県前橋市大手町一丁目１番１号 |ncid=BC14492681 |doi=10.24484/sitereports.121895 |publisher= |pages=78-80}}</ref>

== Deities ==
The shrine enshrines the following three deities:<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|和書 |title=吉岡村誌 |date=1980-11-15 |year=1980 |publisher=吉岡村教育委員会 |pages=925-928 |editor=吉岡村誌編纂室}}</ref><ref name=":0" />
* {{ill|Hoori|ja|ホオリ|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Toyotama-hime|ja|トヨタマヒメ|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Sukunabikona|ja|スクナビコナ|12=draft}}

The {{ill|Shintai|ja|神体|1=Shintai|12=draft}} is a single-wood-carved statue of {{ill|Ekādaśamukha|lt=Eleven-faced Kannon|ja|十一面観音|12=draft}}, estimated to be from the {{ill|Muromachi period|ja|室町時代|12=draft}} and standing 90 cm tall.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> According to the ''{{ill|Shintōshū|ja|神道集|12=draft}}'', the {{ill|Honji Suijaku|ja|本地仏|12=draft}} of Ikaho Shrine is an Eleven-faced Kannon, matching this description.

== History ==
=== Establishment ===
[[File:伊香保神社 Ikaho shrine - panoramio.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|{{ill|Ikaho Shrine|ja|伊香保神社|12=draft}} ({{ill|Shibukawa, Gunma|ja|渋川市|12=draft}})}}{{small|Located in the {{ill|Ikaho Onsen|ja|伊香保温泉|12=draft}} area, Sannomiya Shrine serves as its Satomiya.}}
The shrine is traditionally believed to have been established in {{ill|Tenpyō Shōhō|ja|天平勝宝|12=draft}} 2 (750 CE), though detailed records are lacking.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />

In medieval times, the ''Shintōshū'' describes the "Ikaho Daimyōjin" as having a female form enshrined at the Satomiya in Sannomiya Shibukawa, with its honji being the Eleven-faced Kannon. This suggests Sannomiya Shrine served as the Satomiya of {{ill|Ikaho Shrine|ja|伊香保神社|12=draft}} (Yuzen Shrine) in {{ill|Shibukawa, Gunma|ja|渋川市|12=draft}}.<ref name=":1" /> 

