'''Sannomiya Shrine''' (三宮神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located in {{ill|Yoshioka, Gunma|ja|吉岡町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshioka, Gunma|qq=}}, {{ill|Kitagunma District|ja|北群馬郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitagunma District|qq=}}, {{ill|Gunma Prefecture|ja|群馬県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gunma Prefecture|qq=}}. It is a {{ill|Shikinai-sha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinai-sha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} ({{ill|Myōjin Taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōjin Taisha|qq=}}) and Ranked as the third shrine ({{ill|Sannomiya|ja|三宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sannomiya|qq=}}) of {{ill|Kōzuke Province|ja|上野国|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōzuke Province|qq=}}. Its former shrine Rank was {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|村社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village Shrine|qq=}}.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|和書 |first= |last=群馬県地域創生部文化財保護課 |title=群馬県近世寺社総合調査報告書－歴史的建造物を中心に－神社編 |origdate=2022-03-18 |date=2022-03-18 |url=https://sitereports.nabunken.go.jp/121895 |location=群馬県前橋市大手町一丁目１番１号 |ncid=BC14492681 |doi=10.24484/sitereports.121895 |publisher= |pages=78-80}}</ref>

== Deities ==
The shrine enshrines the following three deities:<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|和書 |title=吉岡村誌 |date=1980-11-15 |year=1980 |publisher=吉岡村教育委員会 |pages=925-928 |editor=吉岡村誌編纂室}}</ref><ref name=":0" />
* {{ill|Hoori|ja|ホオリ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hoori|qq=}}
* {{ill|Toyotama-hime|ja|トヨタマヒメ|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyotama-hime|qq=}}
* {{ill|Sukunabikona|ja|スクナビコナ|1=Sukunabikona|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukunabikona|qq=}}

The {{ill|Shintai|ja|神体|1=Shintai|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shintai|13=User:Immanuelle/Shintai|qq=}} is a single-wood-carved statue of {{ill|Ekādaśamukha|lt=Eleven-faced Kannon|ja|十一面観音|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ekādaśamukha|qq=}}, estimated to be from the {{ill|Muromachi period|ja|室町時代|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Muromachi period|qq=}} and standing 90 cm tall.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> According to the ''{{ill|Shintōshū|ja|神道集|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shintōshū|qq=}}'', the {{ill|Honji Suijaku|ja|本地仏|1=Honji_suijaku#Honji Buddha|lt=Honji Buddha|2=ja|3=本地垂迹|4=fr|5=Honji suijaku|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Honji Suijaku|13=User:Immanuelle/Honji_suijaku#Honji Buddha|qq=}} of Ikaho Shrine is an Eleven-faced Kannon, matching this description.

== History ==
=== Establishment ===
[[File:伊香保神社 Ikaho shrine - panoramio.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|{{ill|Ikaho Shrine|ja|伊香保神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikaho Shrine|qq=}} ({{ill|Shibukawa, Gunma|ja|渋川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa, Gunma|qq=}})}}{{small|Located in the {{ill|Ikaho Onsen|ja|伊香保温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikaho Onsen|qq=}} area, Sannomiya Shrine serves as its Satomiya.}}
The shrine is traditionally believed to have been established in {{ill|Tenpyō Shōhō|ja|天平勝宝|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpyō Shōhō|qq=}} 2 (750 CE), though detailed records are lacking.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />

In medieval times, the ''Shintōshū'' describes the "Ikaho Daimyōjin" as having a female form enshrined at the Satomiya in Sannomiya Shibukawa, with its honji being the Eleven-faced Kannon. This suggests Sannomiya Shrine served as the Satomiya of {{ill|Ikaho Shrine|ja|伊香保神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikaho Shrine|qq=}} (Yuzen Shrine) in {{ill|Shibukawa, Gunma|ja|渋川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa, Gunma|qq=}}.<ref name=":1" /> 

