In medieval times, the ''Shintōshū'' describes the "Ikaho Daimyōjin" as having a female form enshrined at the Satomiya in Sannomiya Shibukawa, with its honji being the Eleven-faced Kannon. This suggests Sannomiya Shrine served as the Satomiya of {{ill|Ikaho Shrine|ja|伊香保神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikaho Shrine|qq=}} (Yuzen Shrine) in [[:en:Shibukawa, Gunma|Shibukawa, Gunma]].<ref name=":1" /> 

