'''Sannomiya Shrine''' (三宮神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Yoshioka, Gunma|Yoshioka, Gunma]], [[:en:Kitagunma District, Gunma|Kitagunma District]], [[:en:Gunma Prefecture|Gunma Prefecture]]. It is a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} ({{ill|Myōjin Taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōjin Taisha|qq=}}) and Ranked as the third shrine ([[:en:Sannomiya|Sannomiya]]) of [[:en:Kōzuke Province|Kōzuke Province]]. Its former shrine Rank was {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|村社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village Shrine|qq=}}.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|和書 |first= |last=群馬県地域創生部文化財保護課 |title=群馬県近世寺社総合調査報告書－歴史的建造物を中心に－神社編 |origdate=2022-03-18 |date=2022-03-18 |url=https://sitereports.nabunken.go.jp/121895 |location=群馬県前橋市大手町一丁目１番１号 |ncid=BC14492681 |doi=10.24484/sitereports.121895 |publisher= |pages=78-80}}</ref>

== Deities ==
The shrine enshrines the following three deities:<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|和書 |title=吉岡村誌 |date=1980-11-15 |year=1980 |publisher=吉岡村教育委員会 |pages=925-928 |editor=吉岡村誌編纂室}}</ref><ref name=":0" />
* [[:en:Hoori|Hoori]]
* [[:en:Toyotama-hime|Toyotama-hime]]
* [[:en:Sukunabikona|Sukunabikona]]

The [[:en:Shintai|Shintai]] is a single-wood-carved statue of [[:en:Ekādaśamukha|Eleven-faced Kannon]], estimated to be from the [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi period]] and standing 90 cm tall.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> According to the ''[[:en:Shintōshū|Shintōshū]]'', the {{ill|Honji Suijaku|ja|本地仏|1=Honji_suijaku#Honji Buddha|lt=Honji Buddha|2=ja|3=本地垂迹|4=fr|5=Honji suijaku|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Honji Suijaku|13=User:Immanuelle/Honji_suijaku#Honji Buddha|qq=}} of Ikaho Shrine is an Eleven-faced Kannon, matching this description.

