'''Sannomiya Shrine''' (三宮神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Yoshioka, Gunma|Yoshioka, Gunma]], [[:en:Kitagunma District, Gunma|Kitagunma District]], [[:en:Gunma Prefecture|Gunma Prefecture]]. It is a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|lt=Shikinaisha}} ({{ill|Myōjin Taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myōjin Taisha|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}) and Ranked as the third shrine ([[:en:Sannomiya|Sannomiya]]) of [[:en:Kōzuke Province|Kōzuke Province]]. Its former shrine Rank was {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|村社|1=Son-sha|qid=Q134917284}}{{efn|Former shrine rank|lt=Son-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}}.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|和書 |first= |last=群馬県地域創生部文化財保護課 |title=群馬県近世寺社総合調査報告書－歴史的建造物を中心に－神社編 |origdate=2022-03-18 |date=2022-03-18 |url=https://sitereports.nabunken.go.jp/121895 |location=群馬県前橋市大手町一丁目１番１号 |ncid=BC14492681 |doi=10.24484/sitereports.121895 |publisher= |pages=78-80}}</ref>

== Deities ==
The shrine enshrines the following three deities:<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|和書 |title=吉岡村誌 |date=1980-11-15 |year=1980 |publisher=吉岡村教育委員会 |pages=925-928 |editor=吉岡村誌編纂室}}</ref><ref name=":0" />
* [[:en:Hoori|Hoori]]
* [[:en:Toyotama-hime|Toyotama-hime]]
* [[:en:Sukunabikona|Sukunabikona]]

The [[:en:Shintai|Shintai]] is a single-wood-carved statue of [[:en:Ekādaśamukha|Eleven-faced Kannon]], estimated to be from the [[:en:Muromachi period|Muromachi period]] and standing 90 cm tall.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> According to the ''[[:en:Shintōshū|Shintōshū]]'', the [[:en:Honji suijaku|Honji Buddha]] of Ikaho Shrine is an Eleven-faced Kannon, matching this description.

== History ==
=== Establishment ===
[[File:伊香保神社 Ikaho shrine - panoramio.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|{{ill|Ikaho Shrine|ja|伊香保神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikaho Shrine|qq=|1=Ikaho Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17220841}} ([[:en:Shibukawa, Gunma|Shibukawa, Gunma]])}}{{small|Located in the {{ill|Ikaho Onsen|ja|伊香保温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikaho Onsen|qq=}} area, Sannomiya Shrine serves as its Satomiya.}}
The shrine is traditionally believed to have been established in [[:en:Tenpyō-shōhō|Tenpyō Shōhō]] 2 (750 CE), though detailed records are lacking.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />

In medieval times, the ''Shintōshū'' describes the "Ikaho Daimyōjin" as having a female form enshrined at the Satomiya in Sannomiya Shibukawa, with its honji being the Eleven-faced Kannon. This suggests Sannomiya Shrine served as the Satomiya of {{ill|Ikaho Shrine|ja|伊香保神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ikaho Shrine|qq=|1=Ikaho Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17220841}} (Yuzen Shrine) in [[:en:Shibukawa, Gunma|Shibukawa, Gunma]].<ref name=":1" /> 

